(51515, 'E7AB9DFA-21BC-4716-9E81-4FAF7987DC40', 'Dear Climb Hire Community,  I️ cannot let this week come to an end without sending a note about the Supreme Court''s decision to overturn Roe V Wade today. It''s a gut wrenching decision that will have impact on women and families for decades to come. The repeal represents a profound rollback of American civil rights. This decision will also disproportionately impact vulnerable communities who don''t have the means to travel to other states for abortions. Fifty years ago, Roe V Wade had a massive impact on women''s ability to become part of the workforce. I️ have watched so many mamas in our community launch careers with deep pride over the last few years. We will obviously continue to support families in every way we can. And we  will also see women struggle as they put themselves at risk unnecessarily. I''m outraged and deeply sad. I️ know many of you are feeling that way too. I️ wish I️ knew what lies ahead. We live in a divided country and I️ assume there will be many who will fight for a long time to get this changed. We are a community of care and action. So please hug each other and support one another through this difficult time in our country''s lifecycle. Wishing you love and strength on days like today. Nitzan  CEO, Climb Hire', 'Nitzan', 'David', '2022-06-24T15:52:14.401556'),
